  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kuapa Kids Camps Child Labour Project (Ghana)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nearly one million children in Ghana work on cocoa farms instead of going to school. Many work very long hours or in hazardous conditions. This project will teach children about their rights, and help them talk to adults about what is expected of the children. It will form groups of children and respected adults to improve the number of children who stay in school, and make people aware of the benefits of an education as opposed to child labour. It aims to help the children do better in school and reduce the number of children working on farms in dangerous conditions, and also to learn from this experience so it can work in more communities.</narrative>
  </description>
